58.6	Philadelphia_Experiment	Philadelphia Experiment	The Philadelphia Experiment is the name of an alleged naval military experiment said to have been carried out at the Philadelphia Naval Shipyard in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, USA sometime around October 28, 1943. It is alleged that the U.S. Navy destroyer escort USS Eldridge was to be rendered invisible (or "cloaked") to enemy devices. The experiment is also referred to as Project Rainbow.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/De173Eldridge.jpg/300px-De173Eldridge.jpg
